7:
Nay, never! I shall spend my life
indoors, indulging in luxury by my
lonesome!
11:
Princess... Is that truly what you
desire?
13:
I can see within your heart a fervent
hope to laugh and smile amongst
friends.
18:
If that is so, strange mirror, then
answer me...
23:
How do I become adorable enough
to seize the hearts of all who gaze
upon me?!
28:
What about changing your
hairstyle? Like so.
34:
Goodness! I look like the peak of
cuteness!
38:
Combining that with attire one may
call "cool" and "stylish"...
43:
Yes! This is perfect! Now I simply
must leave the house to show the
world my beauty!
46:
Show me too! I wanna look cool like
Levy!
49:
Hehe, understood. Could you line up
in an orderly fashion, everyone?
53:
Guess it's no surprise the yokai
performance is a hit. That mirror
really is something else.
56:
Yeah... Knowing that it can do things
like change your makeup and give
you animal ears...
61:
Reminds you of those smartphone
apps, right?
65:
I am satisfied knowing everyone is
enjoying themselves. Would you two
like to try?
71: Oh! I look just like Marina!
76:
H-hold on, I designed this outfit for
Dia! It's not for me...
81:
...Stella, is that the kind of style you
like?
90:
What a resounding success that
was! My thanks, Manoka!
93:
The honor was all mine. I enjoyed
myself immensely—
105:
One that I know from a dream...
Connected through another mirror...
111:
Come on, Sakuya. We'll be in trouble
if any of your old followers spot you.
114:
Why did you tag along anyway? Is
this KoiAzu or whatever really that
important?
118:
If I leave the shopping to you, I know
you'll come home with another
storybook again instead of manga.
123:
Wh-what does it matter? Those are
originally from Shibuya, right? Plus
that pink monster was cute!
127:
I also liked that book very much. I
am pleased to hear that we share
the same tastes.
131:
Who the hell are you? You feel
familiar somehow...
136:
I am glad to see that you are no
longer drowning in your pain.
146:
I don't, but... I feel as if I've seen her in
the mirror somehow...
151:
Well, we were connected for but a
moment.
154:
But in that moment, I wished that
someone could be there to wipe
your tears.
162:
...We are. It seems your wish came
true.
166:
What? What are you two talking
about?
171:
Oh, before I forget, I wanted to offer
you my thanks as well.
174:
I am truly grateful that you broke
Orochi's seal.
184:
Without that, my masters would
have never been freed.
186:
Though I do regret that their
resentment was never alleviated...
191:
...You do realize I could've done so
much more damage if I'd used you,
right?
196:
Should that be your wish now, I will
answer your call.
198:
However, I do not believe you have
need of me.
201:
I would like to speak with you more,
but I have a prior engagement to
attend to.
204:
I hope we can enjoy a meal
together the next time we meet.
215:
...Which is what happened the other
day. Hehe, I enjoyed myself
immensely.
219:
...I only wish I could have been more
help.
223:
You are always helping me, though.
Even now—
228:
This is your last chance. It's our lives
or yours!
233: Why... do you stay your hand...
237:
Because I asked him to. I wished to
speak with you who have deserted
the shogun.
244:
The destruction of this world, to put
an end to the cruelty and ceaseless
suffering of its people.
245:
Could you make that happen,
sacred vessel?
248:
...When I was awoken as Orochi, I felt
it.
251:
The pain of the ninja who were no
longer needed by their masters.
Offered up and abandoned.
254:
Since then, I have become a little
more aware. A little more selfish.
257:
Which is why I would like to make
your deepest wish come true.
260:
I am a mirror, who but reflects your
desires.
263:
Would you care to share your true
feelings with me?
